{"type":"message","id":"3710ec7b","parentId":"9e7d5102","timestamp":"2026-03-25T10:17:28.210Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-aae4ba5e64774a5680e0dfbbf42ebabd","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Eagle-2 VLM Diffusion Transformer policy LeRobot paper\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 6297,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39953cb618eb6e09\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nVision Language Action Models (VLA) & Policies for Robots\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"39953cb618eb6e09\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://learnopencv.com/vision-language-action-models-lerobot-policy/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"43e02a10e163310d\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSystem 2: VLM that interprets phsical ... actions. System 1: <strong>A Diffusion Transformer that follows the instructions of System 2 by denoising to produce meaningful smooth and precise motor actions at 120Hz</strong>....\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"43e02a10e163310d\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"June 9, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"learnopencv.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9b21c00fae11b3c1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGR00T N1: An Open Foundation Model for Generalist Humanoid Robots\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9b21c00fae11b3c1\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://arxiv.org/html/2503.14734v2\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"adc0637270c895a3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>The VLM outputs, together with robot state and action encodings, are passed to the Diffusion Transformer module to generate motor actions</strong>. GR00T N1 is a Vision-Language-Action (VLA) model for humanoid robots trained on diverse data sources. The model contains a vision-language backbone that ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"adc0637270c895a3\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"March 27, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"arxiv.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1ad02df479378c24\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n2025-3-18 GR00T N1: An Open Foundation Model for Generalist Humanoid Robots\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1ad02df479378c24\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://d1qx31qr3h6wln.cloudfront.net/publications/GR00T%20N1%20Whitepaper.pdf\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6df115d6150b9aad\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe VLM outputs, together with robot state and · action encodings, are passed to the Di\\u001dusion Transformer module to generate motor actions. ... GR00T N1 is a Vision-Language-Action (VLA) model for humanoid robots trained on diverse data sources. The model contains a vision-language backbone that encodes language and image input and a DiT-based · \\u001eow-matching policy that outputs high-frequency actions. We use the NVIDIA Eagle-2 VLM (Li et al., 2025) as\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6df115d6150b9aad\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"d1qx31qr3h6wln.cloudfront.net\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cf42e9059e45d596\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nπ0: A Vision-Language-Action Flow Model for General Robot Control\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cf42e9059e45d596\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.pi.website/download/pi0.pdf\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8adf08e693335a3\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFig. 1: Our generalist robot policy uses a pre-trained vision-language model (VLM) backbone, as well as a diverse cross-\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d8adf08e693335a3\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.pi.website\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"330c067494107636\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDiffusion Policy: Transformer backbone support · Issue #624 · huggingface/lerobot\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"330c067494107636\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot/issues/624\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e1bcbed378b8c14a\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nEven in their paper, they claimed that <strong>the transformer seems to be not as good and stable as Unet backbone</strong>, but from my previous reproduce and others work, it is not quite true to claim transformer is worse (no matter the number of params).\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e1bcbed378b8c14a\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"github.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Eagle-2 VLM Diffusion Transformer policy LeRobot paper","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":6297,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"39953cb618eb6e09\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nVision Language Action Models (VLA) & Policies for Robots\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"39953cb618eb6e09\">>>","url":"https://learnopencv.com/vision-language-action-models-lerobot-policy/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"43e02a10e163310d\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSystem 2: VLM that interprets phsical ... actions. System 1: <strong>A Diffusion Transformer that follows the instructions of System 2 by denoising to produce meaningful smooth and precise motor actions at 120Hz</strong>....\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"43e02a10e163310d\">>>","published":"June 9, 2025","siteName":"learnopencv.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9b21c00fae11b3c1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nGR00T N1: An Open Foundation Model for Generalist Humanoid Robots\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9b21c00fae11b3c1\">>>","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2503.14734v2","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"adc0637270c895a3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>The VLM outputs, together with robot state and action encodings, are passed to the Diffusion Transformer module to generate motor actions</strong>. GR00T N1 is a Vision-Language-Action (VLA) model for humanoid robots trained on diverse data sources. The model contains a vision-language backbone that ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"adc0637270c895a3\">>>","published":"March 27, 2025","siteName":"arxiv.org"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1ad02df479378c24\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n2025-3-18 GR00T N1: An Open Foundation Model for Generalist Humanoid Robots\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1ad02df479378c24\">>>","url":"https://d1qx31qr3h6wln.cloudfront.net/publications/GR00T%20N1%20Whitepaper.pdf","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6df115d6150b9aad\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe VLM outputs, together with robot state and · action encodings, are passed to the Di\u001dusion Transformer module to generate motor actions. ... GR00T N1 is a Vision-Language-Action (VLA) model for humanoid robots trained on diverse data sources. The model contains a vision-language backbone that encodes language and image input and a DiT-based · \u001eow-matching policy that outputs high-frequency actions. We use the NVIDIA Eagle-2 VLM (Li et al., 2025) as\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6df115d6150b9aad\">>>","siteName":"d1qx31qr3h6wln.cloudfront.net"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cf42e9059e45d596\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nπ0: A Vision-Language-Action Flow Model for General Robot Control\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"cf42e9059e45d596\">>>","url":"https://www.pi.website/download/pi0.pdf","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d8adf08e693335a3\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFig. 1: Our generalist robot policy uses a pre-trained vision-language model (VLM) backbone, as well as a diverse cross-\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d8adf08e693335a3\">>>","siteName":"www.pi.website"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"330c067494107636\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDiffusion Policy: Transformer backbone support · Issue #624 · huggingface/lerobot\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"330c067494107636\">>>","url":"https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot/issues/624","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e1bcbed378b8c14a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nEven in their paper, they claimed that <strong>the transformer seems to be not as good and stable as Unet backbone</strong>, but from my previous reproduce and others work, it is not quite true to claim transformer is worse (no matter the number of params).\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e1bcbed378b8c14a\">>>","siteName":"github.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774433848199}}
